<Chapter
 id="2"
>
<Paragraph
 id="2.1"
 guid="49369c23-ccd1-4131-b01e-42cbbf3a36f3"
 type="TITLE"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>General<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.1.1.1"
 guid="97f12209-d1b7-4e8a-a4e2-3288c14f780e"
 type="DEFINITION"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>This chapter describes the functional requirements on all information which is exchanged between ERTMS/ETCS onboard and the Vehicle via the Train Interface.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.1.1.2"
 guid="53acd6ba-79b4-4e17-a613-759cd440eb4b"
 type="DEFINITION"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The information which is exchanged between ERTMS/ETCS onboard and the Vehicle is based on the functionality defined by the ERTMS/ETCS SRS [1]</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.1.1.3"
 guid="ad1c2fc2-3eec-4076-b323-52d765bce3a8"
 type="DEFINITION"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note: Due to its complexity and characteristics, the specification of the interface between ERTMS/ETCS onboard and the recording device in the train is defined in a separate interface specification and therefore not part of the train interface specification.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.1.1.4"
 guid="ce143023-d9f6-4de4-8e42-6e8d7ea36cef"
 type="DEFINITION"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>With reference to the Train Interface:
- Input is defined as data flow from Vehicle to ERTMS/ETCS onboard
- Output is defined as data flow from ERTMS/ETCS onboard to Vehicle.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.1.1.5"
 guid="a5661e0f-3e68-4fe9-8013-a0c212879ec8"
 type="DEFINITION"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>In this chapter all functional requirements are written as mandatory principles, i.e. using the word &quot;shall&quot;. Whether a function is used in a specific implementation of the Train Interface may depend on the characteristics of the Vehicle.</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.2"
 guid="b2e0f352-0c2b-4677-879f-b71184656510"
 type="TITLE"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Mode Control<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.2.1"
 guid="d186606f-8953-45ed-8dcd-3e5505d8921e"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Sleeping<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.2.1.1"
 guid="9bd34b9e-1275-4b1d-b8bd-f7d43514a97f"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The sleeping information is defined as a two state input with the following values:
- Sleeping requested
- Sleeping not requested.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.2.1.2"
 guid="705d58b9-e6bf-4033-9442-3c725365f693"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note: The input value &quot;Sleeping requested&quot; is used by ERTMS/ETCS onboard as one of the conditions for the transition to Sleeping mode. The other two conditions are &quot;standstill&quot;, which is managed internally in the ERTMS/ETCS onboard and &quot;All desks connected to the ERTMS/ETCS onboard equipment are closed&quot;, equivalent to &quot;All cabs connected to the ERTMS/ETCS onboard equipment are not active&quot;, which is generated internally in the ERTMS/ETCS onboard based on the input values &quot;Cab not active&quot; as defined in 2.5.1 of this document. See also the SRS references in 2.8.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.2.1.3"
 guid="799f51a4-a983-491f-96a4-c53a0a152fcf"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The following requirements shall apply to the rolling stock:<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.2.1.3.1"
 guid="b56eebb1-e09a-44c9-8cb4-a786a164af3d"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>After successful train inauguration, i.e. one master vehicle exists, defined by strictly one activated cab in the train, the information about successful master definition shall be communicated train-wide to all ERTMS/ETCS onboard units by means of the value &quot;Sleeping requested&quot;.<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.2.1.3.1.1"
 guid="6e7ef4e6-2a10-45f0-b613-1dea421cea9a"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Exception: The ERTMS/ETCS onboard connected via the cab status input (see 2.5.1) with the active cab may be excluded from getting the &quot;Sleeping requested&quot; information because it is not relevant for this ERTMS/ETCS onboard.</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.2.1.3.2"
 guid="2a74e194-a693-42bc-bac7-ff75e7e642d9"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>If no active cab exists in the train, this information shall be communicated train-wide to all ERTMS/ETCS onboard units by means of the value &quot;Sleeping not requested&quot;.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.2.1.3.3"
 guid="ac3ce3fc-a133-44c2-9895-2f775ee38a32"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note: By means of this configuration of the sleeping input it is ensured that the ERTMS/ETCS onboard will only go to sleeping mode if another cab in the train is active, i.e. another train control system (ETCS or national) provides the supervision of the train movement.</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.2.2"
 guid="9f83e2e9-455d-4df6-b073-0a27cf795409"
 type="TITLE"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NotImplementable"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Passive shunting<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.2.2.1"
 guid="1e916e21-6a94-4e75-aeaa-8857ea37acf7"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 reviewed="TRUE"
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The passive shunting information is defined as a two state input with the following values:
- Passive shunting permitted
- Passive shunting not permitted.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.2.2.2"
 guid="df56552b-73ea-4617-bea7-d04ca4234fc4"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note: The input value &quot;Passive shunting permitted&quot; is used by ERTMS/ETCS onboard as one of the conditions for the transition to Passive Shunting mode. The other two conditions are &quot;desks are closed&quot;, equivalent to &quot;Cabs are not active&quot;, which is generated internally in the ERTMS/ETCS onboard from the input values &quot;cab not active&quot; as defined in 2.5.1 of this document, and &quot;Continue Shunting on desk closure function
is active, which is generated internally in ERTMS/ETCS onboard from driver input. See also the SRS references in 2.7.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.2.2.3"
 guid="862f1a9f-29cf-477d-8dc2-3633d185d9f0"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The following requirements shall apply to the rolling stock:<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.2.2.3.1"
 guid="42eee8e4-4471-4c2f-83fe-e6bf28a8d931"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The passive shunting input shall have the value &quot;Passive shunting permitted&quot; if one of the following conditions is fulfilled:

a) Vehicle local (i.e. no data communication between vehicles in the train requested): full service brake applied AND drivers train brake controller isolated (for enabling the release of the train brake in other cab);
OR

b) Train-wide (i.e. data communication between vehicles in the train requested): Brakes other than the train brake applied (e.g. holding or parking brake), IF they can be released by train-wide command.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.2.2.3.2"
 guid="33aa9df2-40c2-4f63-b9c2-a54ade97c129"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>If none of the conditions in 2.2.2.3.1 is fulfilled, the passive shunting input shall have the value &quot;Passive shunting not permitted&quot;.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.2.2.3.3"
 guid="9c2f013f-9e3e-490c-b219-39ac7e225169"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>It shall be allowed to configure the passive shunting input permanently as &quot;Passive shunting not permitted&quot;. This is a decision made only by the Railway Undertaking e.g. based on the characteristics of the vehicle.</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.2.3"
 guid="091e2914-e7c9-49ef-ba1c-5ac451504f66"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Non-Leading<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.2.3.1"
 guid="99c18997-e909-4f87-bb31-4cb0656ef216"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The non-leading information is defined as a two state input with the following values:
. Non-leading permitted . Non-leading not permitted.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.2.3.2"
 guid="14a0113e-9a92-4745-9790-56bec28eace5"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note: The input value &quot;Non-leading permitted&quot; is used by ERTMS/ETCS onboard as one of the conditions for the transition to Non Leading mode. The other two conditions are &quot;standstill&quot; and &quot;Driver selects Non Leading via the DMI&quot; which are managed internally in the ERTMS/ETCS onboard. See also the SRS references in 2.7</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.2.3.3"
 guid="a21c883a-a992-4665-9932-013fbeb1ec43"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The following requirements shall apply to the rolling stock:<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.2.3.3.1"
 guid="b40055a7-7ed7-4290-a3d5-2db0e2529f84"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The non-leading input shall have the value &quot;Non-leading permitted&quot; if the following conditions are fulfilled:

a) Drivers train brake controller isolated
AND

b) Travel direction selected</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.2.3.3.2"
 guid="f69d81ce-4490-417c-a6d5-bf202234d2a4"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>If at least one of the conditions in 2.2.3.3.1 is not fulfilled, the non-leading input shall have the value &quot;Non-leading not permitted&quot;.</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.2.4"
 guid="dcd3333c-90b6-4f84-a97e-aab1835d5a6a"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Isolation<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.2.4.1"
 guid="e14a2a36-a1c5-4316-b05f-600097f91329"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The isolation information is defined as a two state output with the following values:
. ETCS isolated . ETCS not isolated.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.2.4.2"
 guid="e39e401b-dc61-47be-aa16-9c916012cf8d"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note: The isolation output is generated by ERTMS/ETCS onboard to inform the Vehicle that the ERTMS/ETCS onboard is in Isolation mode. This information may be used e.g. to isolate the ERTMS/ETCS onboard from brakes and from some other onboard equipment/systems (see SRS clause 4.4.3.1.1).</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3"
 guid="814737d5-1a86-4bc4-9487-077e479240c8"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Control of Brakes<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.3.1"
 guid="034e0620-6023-43a2-ab1a-115b716201a8"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Service brake command<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.3.1.1"
 guid="329a7f27-1bd7-4cd4-a3c6-c54b2e0342d5"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The service brake command (SBC) is defined as a two state output with the following values:
. Service brake commanded . Service brake not commanded.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.1.2"
 guid="bfc16fe6-2364-4975-8d7c-ad98326d1b25"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note: The SBC output is generated by ERTMS/ETCS onboard to command the service brake and to revoke this command.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.1.3"
 guid="1af2e78a-61fe-4a2d-ad86-a2caa3590b0f"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The following requirements shall apply to the rolling stock:<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.3.1.3.1"
 guid="7057d9c0-dca3-4254-b52a-4bfe92452fd5"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The SBC output value &quot;Service brake commanded&quot; shall result in the train applying the full service brake and cutting off the traction.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.1.3.2"
 guid="a0b5a287-67d7-43ea-aae5-37e7772e2f87"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note: Full service brake means application of 100% of the installed braking performance of the train.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.1.3.3"
 guid="8ecd522b-24a8-4154-98cb-742652adcf99"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The SBC output value &quot;Service brake not commanded&quot; shall result in a release of the service brake, but only to the highest brake level currently commanded by other application(s) or by the driver, and shall permit the traction power to be switched on.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.1.3.4"
 guid="ac74e4b9-5cb6-496f-84cc-b63c7437e7b5"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note 1: the traction power can be switched on again only after the driver has cancelled the traction command (i.e. after a 0-position-acknowledgement by the traction controller).</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.1.3.5"
 guid="e160c73d-094f-4a38-a4a6-7f4a98f5433a"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note 2: In case of no SB manually applied by the driver and in case of no ASC activated, the SB released by ETCS will automatically cancel the brake application on the train. In case of a gradient, it is possible to have forward movement which must be controlled by driver with his own action on brake. This is acceptable as it is the same situation today (without ETCS).</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.1.3.6"
 guid="9f0f9ecc-0e79-4748-acf2-c97c8d29ac54"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note 3: The full service brake may be actuated by various brake systems depending on the rolling stock brake architecture (e.g. dynamic brake by substitution, blending or superposition principle with the UIC air brake).</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.2"
 guid="a9d51997-df83-491d-b523-507aa41e1869"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Brake pressure<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.3.2.1"
 guid="f549b249-bf4b-4d17-a7cb-df8b47ffd37a"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The brake pressure information is defined as a composite input with the following values:
. A range from 0 to 6 bar in steps of 0.1 bar.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.2.2"
 guid="6ea52912-6ef6-43dd-93a4-8cd0603b56a0"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note: The brake pressure input is used by ERTMS/ETCS onboard in the service brake feedback model in [1].</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.2.3"
 guid="93872585-4e30-4066-adef-81780918cf64"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The following requirements apply to the rolling stock:<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.3.2.3.1"
 guid="5da99ec2-7aab-47ef-840b-e8b05116f1ba"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The value of the brake pressure input shall represent either the pressure in the main brake pipe or in the brake cylinder.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.2.3.2"
 guid="15427759-9430-4f02-9810-ccbd8e230f0a"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note: The ERTMS/ETCS onboard has to be configured for one of these two input parameters.</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.3"
 guid="5b3f7b30-729f-470e-93d0-2e3eff9fe65c"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Emergency brake command<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.3.3.1"
 guid="07aa4451-7a3c-41ac-8176-3eab54039e3c"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The emergency brake command (EBC) is defined as a two state output with the following values:
. Emergency brake commanded . Emergency brake not commanded.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.3.2"
 guid="983169a7-091c-42ff-9ade-6b4e7172f06b"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note: The EBC output is generated by ERTMS/ETCS onboard to command the emergency brake and to revoke this command.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.3.3"
 guid="84d96d30-43e3-4203-ae6f-6648bd02f4d0"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The following requirements apply to the rolling stock:<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.3.3.3.1"
 guid="5552dcbb-67b4-4719-b7ea-74d92fa3a017"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The EBC output value &quot;Emergency brake commanded&quot; shall result in the train applying the emergency brake and cutting off the traction.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.3.3.2"
 guid="3c432473-4ad8-4b8c-aea0-3fe0b4e9aad6"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The EBC output value &quot;Emergency brake not commanded&quot; shall permit release of the emergency brake (implementation dependent if brake is released automatically or not, decision made by operator) and shall permit the traction power to be switched on.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.3.3.3"
 guid="e3a8fa70-ac9d-45d1-be1e-92747ea4e865"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note: the traction power can be switched on again only after the driver has cancelled the traction command (i.e. after a 0-position-acknowledgement by the traction controller).</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.4"
 guid="914024d3-6bf6-43ef-a347-66f1c951a253"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Special brake inhibit  Trackside orders<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.3.4.1"
 guid="aa3a7b1e-3003-4547-8cc7-6f9f347fdb76"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>To be harmonized.</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.5"
 guid="1b4c3637-6b1b-404c-a8e6-7efa3937c9a3"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Special brake inhibit  STM Orders<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.3.5.1"
