 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The generic requirement descriptions in this section shall apply to the inhibition of the following special brakes:
. Regenerative brake . Magnetic shoe brake . Eddy current brake for emergency braking . Eddy current brake for service braking.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.5.2"
 guid="ee8241a4-8aa5-4163-8de2-20ca4e6ad70a"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>This special brake information is defined for each special brake as a two state output with the following values:
. Not inhibited . Inhibited.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.5.3"
 guid="d191b4a8-10a8-438c-845b-17487db311f9"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note: This special brake inhibit output is generated by the ERTMS/ETCS onboard to inform the train that the respective special brake application is to be allowed / inhibited due to an order from STM.</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
