 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The generic requirement descriptions in this section shall apply to the status of the following special brakes:
. Regenerative brake . Magnetic shoe brake . Eddy current brake . Electro Pneumatic (EP) brake.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.6.2"
 guid="b71f094b-9dd3-45f5-92f3-a39fd870cb1b"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note: The specifications for the status of these special brakes are exactly the same and therefore given only once.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.6.3"
 guid="dc456af4-f303-4870-a171-ef1d7085b9c0"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The special brake status information is defined as a two state input with the following values:
. Special brake active . Special brake not active.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.6.4"
 guid="03cde933-89e7-47e7-9145-df57f955e647"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note: The special brake status input is used by ERTMS/ETCS onboard to adapt the braking curve model for the characteristics of the service brake, the emergency brake, or both, according to the possible configurations of ERTMS/ETCS onboard as defined in [1].</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.6.5"
 guid="c10c7a8f-70ce-4a76-b38d-ef0e3af3f318"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The following requirements shall apply to the rolling stock:<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.3.6.5.1"
 guid="58591906-95a2-4114-9175-01e04940dee2"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The special brake status input shall have the value &quot;Special brake active&quot; if the special brake is available, i.e. in working condition and not inhibited.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.6.5.2"
 guid="80c833b6-8a72-48eb-a0e2-97457bbcb4b1"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The special brake status input shall have the value &quot;Special brake not active&quot; if the special brake is not available, i.e. not in working condition or inhibited.</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.7"
