 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The additional brake status information (ABS) is defined as a two state input with the following values:
. Additional brakes active . Additional brakes not active.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.7.2"
 guid="dd174716-d385-4fbd-be0e-1ccf329bf059"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The &quot;additional brakes&quot; are defined as any brakes in the train which are independent of wheel/rail adhesion.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.7.3"
 guid="cb88b506-7ed8-46a9-988e-3cd7ea95ef7a"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note: The ABS input is used by ERTMS/ETCS onboard to adapt the braking curve model for the characteristics of the additional brakes independent of wheel/rail adhesions, as defined in [1].</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.7.4"
 guid="7bbe637f-9628-42d7-bce5-a76b54030eb6"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The following requirements shall apply to the rolling stock:<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.3.7.4.1"
 guid="9009bf82-5cb0-4f38-98a1-c69ce36d3845"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The ABS input shall have the value &quot;additional brakes active&quot; if the additional brake(s) is/are available, i.e. in working condition and not inhibited.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.3.7.4.2"
 guid="3dafa686-a62d-4a1b-914d-8f8745423727"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The ABS input shall have the value &quot;additional brakes not active&quot; if the additional brake(s) is/are not available, i.e. not in working condition or inhibited.</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
