 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Traction Cut Off<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.4.9.1"
 guid="150c63c0-f112-408f-bb6c-1ea9c8c0d98a"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The traction cut off information (TCO) is defined as a two state output with the following values:
. Cut off traction . Do not cut off traction.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.4.9.2"
 guid="54fc5d9e-849c-4ae7-9f7d-bfcfe12ee72d"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note: The TCO output is generated by ERTMS/ETCS onboard to cut the traction as soon as it passes the warning limit of the braking curve model as defined in [1] or as a consequence of an STM command.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.4.9.3"
 guid="550956f7-ac7b-43c3-9178-93eca2e03bec"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The following requirements shall apply to the rolling stock:<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.4.9.3.1"
 guid="70e73fa7-dc62-4ac5-815d-6b05f9b4b92a"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The TCO output value &quot;Cut off traction&quot; shall be used by the train to cut off the traction power.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.4.9.3.2"
 guid="3ddb9299-36d8-4adf-b558-944c610e4089"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The TCO output value &quot;Do not cut off traction&quot; shall allow the driver or an automatic system (ASC) to apply traction power.</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
