 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Train Status<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.5.1"
 guid="72bb26e2-61ee-4ecc-ae7d-d504b3f11cca"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Cab Status<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.1"
 guid="deed4628-97e4-4181-8665-7509256de3fa"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The cab status information is defined as a two state input with the following values:
. Cab active . Cab not active.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.2"
 guid="4e985ff8-d185-48ce-8afd-6944a286b13a"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note 1: The cab status input is used by ERTMS/ETCS onboard for various purposes as defined in [1] or by an STM as defined in [3]. The expression &quot;desk open&quot; in [1] is equivalent to &quot;Cab active&quot; and &quot;desk closed&quot; in [1] is equivalent to &quot;Cab not active&quot;.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.3"
 guid="839d8340-fe74-4358-8e90-bbcbf37f22e7"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>If there is more than one cab connected to a single ERTMS/ETCS onboard unit, each cab will be connected to its individual input.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.4"
 guid="4c089ca6-3a79-4335-bf6b-23d8dcc52b67"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The following requirements shall apply to the rolling stock:<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.4.1"
 guid="940fcf76-9d94-4edc-9b7f-15982740e30b"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The cab status input shall have the value &quot;Cab active&quot; if the cab connected to this input is active.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.4.2"
 guid="a6becdcf-9e47-4430-b668-fe727b9e29e9"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note: The active cab is the cab from which the traction is controlled.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.4.3"
 guid="6ace0263-f3e3-4b80-802f-7ef76f67ec2d"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The cab status input shall have the value &quot;Cab not active&quot; if the cab connected to this input is not active.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.4.4"
 guid="2285ede8-d6ee-4335-ad56-8651d6bcf99c"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>For single cab locos with two desks, each related to a different train orientation, each desk will be connected to its individual cab status input.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.4.5"
 guid="639e4b78-6508-4b15-8ce2-176c73314ca5"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>For single cab locos with only one desk, the cab status shall be combined with the train orientation information to define two virtual cab status signals, connected to their individual inputs.
Virtual Cab A active = (Cab active) AND (train orientation direction A)
Virtual Cab B active = (Cab active) AND (train orientation direction B)</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.4.6"
 guid="f601c872-0d40-422d-a9ed-92b3d10c28c7"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note: The train orientation may be obtained from e.g. the head lights of the train.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.1.4.7"
 guid="afc11076-89df-4f73-ab8a-4305e755d70a"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Regardless of the vehicle layout the rolling stock shall ensure that only one cab or virtual cab is reported active at any time to a single ERTMS/ETCS onboard equipment.</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph></Sub>
</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.2"
 guid="07f598aa-6058-4a7b-8aa9-97df12fe0a1f"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Direction Controller<Sub>
<Paragraph
 id="2.5.2.1"
 guid="4a159c89-1c48-4991-b068-8e3a93337280"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The direction controller information is defined as a three state input with the following values:
. Forward . Neutral . Backward.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.2.2"
 guid="e3570366-8e7e-4a12-b8eb-61b004744ca2"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>The notion of forward direction shall correspond to the train orientation defined by the active (virtual) cab as defined in 2.5.1, i.e. when the direction controller is in forward position, this means that the train movement will be in the direction of the active (virtual) cab.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.2.3"
 guid="bf9fab91-97bd-4886-a748-5fe11405b73f"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>If no cab is active the direction controller information may have any value, but shall be ignored by ERTMS/ETCS onboard.</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.2.4"
 guid="172da1f2-b135-469b-b39a-5f6fb0fabb49"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
 status="NA"
 version="3.0.0"
 functionalBlockName=""
 Name=""
>Note: The direction controller input is used by ERTMS/ETCS onboard to prevent train movement which conflicts with the current position of the direction controller in the active cab and to detect the driver&apos;s intention to reverse, which is one of the conditions for entering Reversing mode. The direction controller input is also used by an STM as defined in [3].</Paragraph><Paragraph
 id="2.5.2.5"
 guid="76bb47ed-0bdf-48a6-b086-399ebf79deca"
 type="REQUIREMENT"
 scope="OBU"
 bl=""
 name=""
